Sentencas: Cobalt-based layered perovskite oxides have been recognized as pioneering cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) due to their fast oxygen diffusion, surface exchange kinetics, and high electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Investigation of a Layered Perovskite for IT-SOFC Cathodes: B-Site Fe-Doped YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ

Sentencas: Herein, we study novel Fe doped layered perovskites, YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+delta (x = 0, 0.25, 0.5, and 0.75) in terms of their structural properties, thermal expansion behavior, electrical properties, and electrochemical performances for potential usage as a cathode.
Titulo: Investigation of a Layered Perovskite for IT-SOFC Cathodes: B-Site Fe-Doped YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ

Sentencas: Among them, YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.75Fe0.25O5+delta (YBSCF25, x = 0.25) not only shows enhanced structural stability but also meets the essential required properties, including an appropriate thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), chemical compatibility with the electrolyte, and suitable electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Investigation of a Layered Perovskite for IT-SOFC Cathodes: B-Site Fe-Doped YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ

Sentencas: Moreover, power density as high as 1.5 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C is achieved for the YBSCF25-GDC composite cathode with a full cell with a dense thin gadolinium doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte and a Ni-GDC composite anode in humidified H-2.
Titulo: Investigation of a Layered Perovskite for IT-SOFC Cathodes: B-Site Fe-Doped YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ

Sentencas: These favorable features highlight the potential of YBSCF25 as a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Investigation of a Layered Perovskite for IT-SOFC Cathodes: B-Site Fe-Doped YBa0.5Sr0.5Co2-xFexO5+δ
